<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; MURPHY'S EIGHT GOALS PACE BREA VICTORY OVER MAGNOLIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sixth-ranked Brea-Olinda scored nine goals in the second quarter and defeated 
host Magnolia, 18-5, in an Orange League water polo opener Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Tad Murphy led the Wildcats (12-1, 1-0) with eight goals, including five in 
the decisive second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea, which is top-ranked in Division XI, shared the league championship with 
the Sentinels last season. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague water polo: 
</P>
<P>
 Cerritos 19, Cypress 10 -- Cypress (5-3) gave up eight third-quarter goals and 
lost at Cerritos. David Watkins had six goals for the Centurions. 
</P>
<P>
 In South Coast League girls' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills 12, Mater Dei 6 -- Fifth-ranked Dana Hills (6-3, 1-0) got key 
performances at No. 2 singles from Summer Tantee, who swept, 6-0, 6-1, 6-1, and 
the No. 1 doubles team of Michele Johnson and Katie Tierney, who also swept, 
6-2, 6-0, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In Sunset League girls' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach 15, Fountain Valley 3 -- Melissa Dillard and Ashley Mawhorter 
swept their singles sets for Huntington Beach (5-3, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In a Century League boys' cross-country meet: 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park 28, El Modena 29 -- Jeremy Mordock led the way for seventh-ranked 
Villa Park (3-1), finishing the 3.1-mile course at Irvine Park in 15 minutes 58 
seconds. Sixth-ranked El Modena is also 3-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In a Century League girls' cross-country meet: 
</P>
<P>
 El Modena 19, Villa Park 39 -- Leslie Burton, Jessica Dahlberg and Tara 
Whitfield finished in a three-way tie for first place to lead fourth-ranked El 
Modena (4-0) over Villa Park (2-2) at Irvine Park. The threesome finished the 
3.1-mile course in 19 minutes 42 seconds. 
</P>
