<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAMS; MARTIN RETURNS AT QUARTERBACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rams signed quarterback Jamie Martin and will release a player -- most 
likely a wide receiver because of the overload at the position -- today to 
officially make room for him on the roster. 
</P>
<P>
 Martin, an undrafted quarterback from Weber State who was on the Ram roster a 
year ago as a third-team player, was released after the exhibition season to 
make room for Tommy Maddox.He will be the team's No. 3 quarterback against 
Green Bay. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Miller, expected to start against the Packers, threw a number of 
well-aimed and strong 20-yard passes Tuesday with trainer Jim Anderson 
watching. Miller is trying to regain arm strength after suffering a shoulder 
injury against the 49ers two weeks ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams were off Tuesday, but given Maddox's limited practice opportunities 
one might have expected the team to take advantage of the free day to provide 
him extra work to prepare him as Miller's backup. It didn't happen, however. 
T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
