<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: BIG CATFISH COULD NET $100 PRIZE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 They aren't pretty, they are neither sleek nor swift and they spend most of 
their time wallowing in the mud. 
</P>
<P>
 But the catfish that will be put into Irvine and Corona lakes this week will 
still be the most popular fish around.  
</P>
<P>
 Both lakes will receive their normal weekly catfish plants, but seven of the 
fish at Irvine and three at Corona will weigh more than 50 pounds apiece. 
</P>
<P>
 The fish will be tagged and if caught, recorded and released, the angler will 
receive a "conservation" award of $100. 
</P>
</TEXT>
