</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: GIRLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Zuzana Stunova 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Rio Mesa 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Tennis 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Sophomore 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Stunova, 15, was visiting the United States this summer 
and liked it so much she decided to stay. Stunova, ranked No. 2 among 
16-year-olds in her native Czech Republic, is an exchange student at Rio Mesa 
and has made an impact for the Spartans.She has won 11 sets without a loss. 
"She has a cannon," Rio Mesa Coach Steve Worthington said of Stunova. "I'm just 
amazed how she can generate power." 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: The 5-foot-5 Stunova kept Rio Mesa close in a 10-8 defeat to 
Marmonte League favorite Camarillo by sweeping three sets at No. 1 singles. The 
highlight was Stunova's 6-4 victory over Monique Allegre. Allegre, ranked 10th 
in Southern California girls' 18-and-under, is considered the area's top high 
school player. 
</P>
</TEXT>
