<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chris Driscoll 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Agoura 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Water polo 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Driscoll, who scored 62 goals last season, has scored 55 
in 13 matches. He is shooting for the school record, 118, set by Terry Polapink 
in 1992.Driscoll is a three-year starter for Royal. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Driscoll outscored perennial power Royal with eight goals in 
a 16-7 victory over the Highlanders last weekend at the San Luis Obispo 
tournament. He scored 14 goals in four tournament matches, helping the Chargers 
to a fourth-place finish. Driscoll also scored six goals in a victory over 
Crespi earlier in the week. A repeat of his performance against Royal on 
Friday, when the teams meet in a Marmonte League match, could help snap the 
Highlanders' 66-match league winning streak. 
</P>
</TEXT>
