<TEXT>
<P>
 A search for a Thousand Oaks girl who never returned from a Sunday hike was 
called off early Tuesday after sheriff's deputies decided she might be a 
runaway, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The search that began Monday night for Lannea Diederichs, 15, in Wildwood Park 
in Thousand Oaks turned up no evidence of foul play and was called off about 2 
a.m. Tuesday, Ventura County Sheriff's Sgt. David Paige said. 
</P>
<P>
 Diederichs' father told deputies that his daughter, who had gone hiking in the 
1,700-acre park Sunday, has run away from home before, and had subsequently 
attended at least one concert by the Grateful Dead rock group. 
</P>
<P>
 The search involved a helicopter and 15 volunteers of the east county search 
and rescue team. GREG RIPPEE 
