<HEADLINE>
<P>
POSITIVE EXPERIENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On Sunday, Sept. 11, I personally spent some seven hours with Nellie the 
elephant at Oktoberfest.She purred with delight, danced with her trainer and 
showed everyone watching how to eat a watermelon -- whole. 
</P>
<P>
 For the first time in my life I was able to appreciate the intelligence and 
friendliness of an elephant. While giving rides, Nellie played with her toys, 
including her "lunch box."  
</P>
<P>
 The only remark that the Los Angeles Times could make was to nit-pick about 
the animal, rather than comment on the positive learning experiences 2,000 
people in attendance witnessed. 
</P>
<P>
 RAGNAR STORM-LARSEN 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
