<HEADLINE>
<P>
HELP'S SERVICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I would like to convey our sincere thanks for the recent article featuring 
HELP of Ojai, Inc. As pleased as we are with the story, there are two important 
points that were not addressed. 
</P>
<P>
 First, it is important to know that we are a United Way of Ventura County 
member agency and have been since 1981.The '94-'95 funding, allocated to HELP 
of Ojai through the United Way allocation process, is $20,000. In addition, we 
receive United Way donor-designated gifts. As important as the financial 
support is, we also gain immeasurably from our overall affiliation with United 
Way and the 60-plus other member agencies. All of us in this county are 
fortunate to have such a strong, viable United Way. 
</P>
<P>
 Second, well-covered was the fact that HELP sponsors many senior programs. 
Missing was information regarding the many services HELP provides for the 
non-senior. HELP was intergenerational long before it became "the in thing." 
Non-seniors are assisted in so many ways, for example, with counseling 
services, a food pantry and an after-school recreation program. 
</P>
<P>
 MARLENE SPENCER 
</P>
<P>
 Ojai 
</P>
</TEXT>
