<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; MAN SOUGHT IN THEFT AT AUTO CLUB OFFICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police on Tuesday were seeking a robber who made off with about $2,000 from a 
local membership-sales office of the Automobile Club of Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
 The robber -- described as a white man in his 40s with gray-streaked dark hair 
and a thick gray mustache -- was last seen running away from the office, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, who said he had a gun, demanded money from a cashier shortly after 4 
p.m. Monday, Lt. Bruce Kelly said. The robber was given about $2,000 in cash 
before he left the office in the 7800 block of Talbert Avenue, Kelly said. 
</P>
