<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; COMPOSITE SKETCH OF RAPIST IS RELEASED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police have released a composite sketch of a man who raped a woman Sept. 27 
after luring her to his parked van on the pretense that his infant had stopped 
breathing. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, a 21-year-old Huntington Beach woman, told investigators that the 
attack took place about 6 p.m. in an alley behind a commercial area at Beach 
Boulevard and Terry Drive.She said the man pushed her inside the late model, 
dark-blue van and held a gun to her head while he assaulted her. She was 
subsequently released at the scene, and the man fled south on Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Police describe the man as Latino, 30 to 35 years old, 5 feet 10 inches tall 
and weighing 180 pounds. He was further described as having dark hair and a 
stubble of beard. He was wearing a turquoise shirt and gray sweat pants. The 
van was described as full-size, possibly a Dodge, with tinted windows and a 
rear-mounted spare-tire rack with no tire.  
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information is asked to contact Huntington Police Detective Dennis 
Branch at (714) 536-5608. MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</TEXT>
