<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: RANCHO SANTA MARGARITA; 4 INCUMBENTS ON SCHOOL BOARDS 
BACKED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The political action committee of the South Orange County Chambers of Commerce 
has endorsed the four incumbents running for reelection to the boards of the 
Saddleback Valley Unified School and Capistrano Unified School districts. 
</P>
<P>
 The incumbents are Dore J. Gilbert and Bobbee Cline in Saddleback Valley, and 
Annette B. Gude and Crystal Kochendorfer in Capistrano Unified. 
</P>
<P>
 The school board endorsements are the first made by the organization in nearly 
a decade. 
</P>
<P>
 Mark Gaughan, chair of the group's candidate selection process, said the 
school board incumbents drew the support of business leaders because of their 
concern over challengers, some of whom are accused of holding views supported 
by the religious right. Such challengers have denied the characterization. 
</P>
<P>
 The South Orange County Chambers of Commerce PAC represents individual 
chambers of commerce in Aliso Viejo, Laguna Hills, Lake Forest, Mission Viejo 
and Rancho Santa Margarita.JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
