<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: MONTEBELLO; SCHOOLS 
CHIEF RESIGNS TO TAKE SALT LAKE CITY JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Montebello schools chief Darline P. Robles has resigned to become 
superintendent of the Salt Lake City School District. 
</P>
<P>
 Robles has held teaching or administrative positions in the Montebello Unified 
School District for 21 years. She became superintendent in July, 1991, and 
helped steer the 32,300-student district away from insolvency.  
</P>
<P>
 Board President Darrell H. Heacock said that Robles, 44, will remain in her 
$97,000-a-year job until at least the end of December to help the district trim 
$10.2 million to balance the budget.  
</P>
<P>
 School officials have demanded that teachers take a pay cut and have asked the 
state to appoint a mediator. 
</P>
</TEXT>
