<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: MALIBU; TEEN-AGER 
STABBED TO DEATH BY 6 MEN AT TOPANGA BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 17-year-old boy was fatally stabbed by six men Tuesday morning while 
visiting Topanga State Beach with a friend, sheriff's officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The boy, whose name was not released, died at Santa Monica Hospital at 12:35 
a.m., approximately half an hour after he was attacked, said sheriff's 
spokesman Gabe Ramirez. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, who apparently was visiting from abroad, and a female companion 
were approached by the men, who had driven into the parking lot in two cars 
near Coastline Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 An argument ensued, and the boy began to run down the beach. The suspects 
tackled him and stabbed him several times, Ramirez said. The boy's friend was 
unharmed. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators do not have a description of the vehicles or the killers. Anyone 
with information about the crime is asked to call the Sheriff's Department at 
(213) 890-5500. 
</P>
</TEXT>
