<HEADLINE>
<P>
HE ALSO HAS AN EYE ON THE RAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Oriole owner Peter Angelos is determined to add another pro sports franchise 
to his portfolio. He is working to bring the Rams to Baltimore, although he 
would certainly be happy to take the Buccaneers out of Tampa Bay. 
</P>
<P>
 "The Baltimore Buccaneers," he said. "I like the sound of that." 
</P>
<P>
 Angelos has a standing offer of $200 million for the franchise, although 
Buccaneer officials said they are not considering bids. With that in mind, 
Angelos has focused his attention on the Rams. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've been working on it for quite a while now, and I would say our chances 
are very good that we will be successful," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Angelos went to Los Angeles last month to continue his negotiations with the 
Rams, who have said they will make a decision in the next month or so. 
</P>
<P>
 Maryland Gov. William Donald Schaefer accompanied Angelos to the meeting with 
the Rams. He left the session with much less optimism than Angelos. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA100594-0134 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 085682 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
October 5, 1994, Wednesday, Southland Edition 
</P>
