<HEADLINE>
<P>
5.8 QUAKE ROCKS EAST COAST OF TAIWAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A strong earthquake rocked Taiwan this morning, breaking windows and shaking 
tiles from buildings in towns along the east coast, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The quake, measuring a magnitude 5.8 and centered 20 miles east of the town of 
Chengkung on the Pacific coast, was felt throughout the island, the Central 
Weather Bureau said. Chengkung is 140 miles south of Taipei. 
</P>
<P>
 A spokesman for the National Police Administration said no reports of injuries 
from the earthquake had been received. 
</P>
</TEXT>
