<P>
 Troll Company Makes Koosh Deal: The creator of the popular Koosh toys has sold 
the company to a New Jersey company that makes troll dolls.Russ Berrie & Co. 
announced this week that it has purchased Oddzon Products for an undisclosed 
price and plans to continue selling the products under the same name. Oddzon 
nets about $30 million annually in revenue on the sale of the popular, 
no-bounce balls made of spaghetti-thin rubber strands, in addition to several 
other spinoff toys. Analysts said Oddzon's market stability may help Russ 
Berrie overcome losses it suffered after its initially popular troll dolls 
fizzled. The $300-million company also designs and sells stuffed animals, 
picture frames and novelty gifts. 
