<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: AUTOS; SOUTH KOREAN MAKER ANNOUNCES DEAL TO PRODUCE KARMANN KIAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by John O'Dell / Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Except for a few restored models and rusted clunkers, the sporty Karmann Ghia 
is a thing of the past.The German-built, Italian-designed car was phased out by 
Volkswagen around 1970. 
</P>
<P>
 But the Karmann Kia will soon be here. South Korean car maker Kia Motors has 
signed a deal with Karmann under which the German sports-car builder will 
assemble 30,000 Karmann Kias a year. 
</P>
<P>
 The company isn't saying anything yet about style or whether any of the cars 
will be imported to the United States by Kia's Irvine-based Kia Motors America 
subsidiary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
