<TEXT>
<P>
 A talk by Cornel West, a professor of religion and African American studies at 
Harvard University, will launch Soka University's Human Rights Lecture Series. 
</P>
<P>
 West, a scholar of institutional racism, is the author of such works as "Race 
Matters," "Keeping Faith: Philosophy of Race in America" and "Prophecy 
Deliverance! An Afro-American Revolutionary Christianity." 
